title: For Sale:  INTERNATIONAL HARVESTER M1 Garand with LMR Barrel Original
postcontent: Up for sale is my all original and fully functional INTERNATIONAL HARVESTER M1 GARAND with the ORIGINAL LMR barrel. LMR made the best barrels that the M1 Garand has ever seen...and if you do some research on the IH M1 Garand, it really has an interesting history. I have it listed under Springfield Armory (SA) because IH wasn't available on the drop box, by the way.The rifle is in excellent condition, with the exception of the original LMR barrel showing throat wear that almost swallows the bullet during the "bullet-test" (I dont' have a gauge at home)--that said, I've fired this rifle several times at an indoor 50 yard range and it is spot-on for accuracy and functionality.I have stripped the full rifle and from everything I can tell, it is 100% original (which explains why the barrel was never replaced) which is pretty darn cool. I can send you as many pictures as you like from my phone/email.Caliber is your standard 30 cal (30-06), and the rifle comes 2 USGI metal cans of original ammo. 1st one is USGI Korean War era marked ammo with a bunch of loose rounds (not sure exact amount, probably over 100 rds. 2nd is WW2 era USGI ammo can with the original repackaging slip from the ammo depot, dated as filled in 1940, and all the ammo is on the original cloth belt for quick loading onto the US Browning .30 cal Machineguns if needed.All rounds are in great condition and you can still hear the powder shake easily inside, test fired a few hundred from the Korean War marked can, all flawlessly fired. The 1940 can is full (250 rds on the original cloth belt). The rifle has very little external wear. No parts aside from LMR and IH from as far as I can tell with a total strip of the rifle. The rifle DOES still have the cartouch on the bottom of the trigger-hand grip, something that I've read typically wears away with use, but hey, mine is still intact so that's awesome. The rifle also comes with an exact reproduction leather 1903 sling and an exact reproduction heavy cloth/nylon sling, both appropriate for the rifle in the WW2 and post-WW2 era. I also have an exact reproduction Olean, NY full-size bayonet for the rifle. I have a ton of pictures that I can send upon request from my phone or from my email.
